x)
For Install Debian on Virtualbox
Virtualization: Utilize VirtualBox to create an isolated lab. This provides a safe space for experimentation without risking the host operating system.
Desktop Environment: XFCE is low resource footprint and high stability.
Post-Installation: Always run sudo apt update immediately after the first boot to synchronize the local package index.

For Basics Commands
Navigation:
pwd: Print Working Directory
ls: List directory contents (Use -l for details, -a for hidden files)
cd: Change directory

File Handling:
mkdir: Create a new directory
touch: Create an empty file
rm: Remove files

Efficiency Shortcuts:
Tab Completion: The single most important skill to save time and prevent typos.
Arrow Keys: Quickly cycle through previously executed commands

Privilege Management: 
sudo is essential for performing administrative tasks, such as installing new software


